So we're like, wait a second.

00:28:24.680 --> 00:28:28.800
We actually can kind of extract this,

00:28:28.960 --> 00:28:30.860
like the act, so like the setting,

00:28:31.140 --> 00:28:33.220
sorry, the arrange, setting up the data,

00:28:33.380 --> 00:28:36.940
the act, like actually making the HTTP request,

00:28:37.640 --> 00:28:40.640
and then the assert, like to ensure the status change

00:28:40.740 --> 00:28:42.960
or that the request go to 200 or something.

00:28:43.060 --> 00:28:44.040
We actually have the data for this.

00:28:45.540 --> 00:28:46.760
And it's reasonably straightforward.

00:28:47.020 --> 00:28:50.220
Like if you capture in, you know, just your like normal,

00:28:50.600 --> 00:28:51.980
like imagine you have a local to-do app

00:28:52.080 --> 00:28:54.620
and you browse like a to-do kind of demo,

00:28:54.900 --> 00:28:56.840
simple to-do app, and you browse to the homepage

00:28:57.020 --> 00:28:58.720
and the homepage maybe lists the to-dos.

00:28:59.840 --> 00:29:01.000
