You know, one of the big,

00:31:24.160 --> 00:31:25.180
one of the things that makes me

00:31:25.380 --> 00:31:27.259
want to write fewer unit tests

00:31:28.160 --> 00:31:30.520
or not write a unit test in a certain case

00:31:31.320 --> 00:31:34.520
is I can test using mocking.

00:31:35.400 --> 00:31:39.580
Given my, let's say, SQLAlchemy or Beanie or whatever,

00:31:40.040 --> 00:31:45.000
Django ORM model, it theoretically matches the database.

00:31:45.560 --> 00:31:47.780
I can do some stuff, set some values and check

00:31:47.780 --> 00:31:48.700
and that's all good.

00:31:49.680 --> 00:31:54.280
But in practice, if the schema in the database

00:31:54.580 --> 00:31:55.980
doesn't match the shape of my object,

00:31:58.040 --> 00:32:00.320
the system freaks out and crashes and says,

00:32:00.460 --> 00:32:01.700
well, that's not going to work, right?

00:32:01.880 --> 00:32:02.320
There's no way.

00:32:02.390 --> 00:32:04.960
And so it doesn't matter how good I mock it out.

00:32:05.110 --> 00:32:09.140
It has to go end to end before I feel very good about it.

00:32:09.390 --> 00:32:11.300
Oh, yeah, okay, it's going to really, really work, right?

00:32:12.290 --> 00:32:12.940
Yeah, exactly.

